title: For Sale/Trade:  Polytech M1a/M14S with Sadlak Mount and new bolt
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is an excellent condition Polytech M1a. Rifle has approximately 500 rounds through it and has ran like a champ. Polytech M1a's are about as close to an actual M1a receiver as you will find. The designs were sold to China in the 80's I believe and their receivers are second to none. Many custom M1a builders will use a Polytech (or Norinco) M1a receiver as a host for a custom build since they are so close to spec. The minor issue with Chicom M1a's is having a soft bolt, so many people will have their bolt replaced with a US made one, like I have. Here's the breakdown of what is on the rifle and the type of work I have had done.

Polytech m14s - $1000
US made LRB bolt - $200
USGI extractor - $10
NM flash hider - $30
Gas piston shim kit (not installed) - $20
Sadlak steel scope mount - $270
Additional tools (usgi m14 combo tool, sadlak gas system wrench) and mags (2x CMI 20-rd and 1x Korean 20-rd) - $100
Harris bipod adapter (not installed, still in bag)- $20

Gunsmithing work done, all work done at Warbirds

Headspace new bolt - $125
Refinish entire rifle - $165
NM trigger job - $50
Install new flash hider - $40

Total money into rifle - $1900 +/- $100 for parts/labor/shipping

All original Chicom parts (including the bolt) will be included in the sale as well as all the M1a goodies I have which includes the sling and an additional polymer stock (all metal included on the stock). I also have a Blackhawk strap on cheek riser that will also come in the sale.  Price includes shipping to your FFL.

The Adams Arms lightweight gas piston conversion kit is a complete retrofitting kit that takes a standard direct gas impingement system AR-15 and converts it with a cooler, cleaner, short stroke gas piston. Installing a piston system on an AR-15 prevents the harmful gas and debris from being sent back in the chamber to cycle the firearm. Piston systems increase overall reliability while also decreasing the amount of maintenance required to keep he firearm operational. This kit can be added to your rifle with no permanent modifications; however some free floating handguard will not be compatible with this system. The manufacturer has a complete list of compatible hand guards.

Includes:
.750" Diameter low profile gas block (Picatinny Gas Block for $35 more)
Gas piston
Piston return spring and bushing
Operating rod
Upper receiver bushing
Installation hardware
1 Piece bolt carrier with integral piston strike face
Bolt spring
Instructions

Fits:
Available for Mid-Length or Carbine Gas System
.750" Diameter Barrel
Adams Arms AR-15 conversion kit system is compatible with .223 Remington/5.56x45mm NATO/6.5x38mm Grendel/6.8x43mm Remington SPC/5.45x39mm
